<HEADLINE>
<P>
'DEALING WITH MISS ETHEL' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I read Al Martinez's column quite frequently and usually like what he writes. 
</P>
<P>
However, his "Dealing With Miss Ethel" upset me and I have a feeling I'm not 
the only one. 
</P>
<P>
I am (for the last 12 years) one of the those "Miss Ethels." I give my time as 
a volunteer working in a hospital gift shop and I think all of us who do this 
kind of work deserve praise. 
</P>
<P>
So most of us are about 70 and over and perhaps our eyesight isn't the best any 
more. We still give of our time and of ourselves. 
</P>
<P>
I think you did "Miss Ethel" and all the rest of us a great injustice. 
</P>
<P>
HELEN MEDAK 
</P>
<P>
North Hollywood 
</P>
</TEXT>
