<P>
SAN DIEGO ZOO EAGLE STOLEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
For the second time in less than two weeks, thieves broke into a locked cage 
and stole a rare bird from the San Diego Zoo. The stolen 30-year-old male 
African bateleur eagle had lived at the zoo since 1961. On June 3, a female 
African milky eagle owl was stolen from a cage about 100 yards away. Zoo 
officials said the thefts apparently were well planned by someone with specific 
knowledge about the birds. There was no evidence the thefts were committed by 
the same people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
