<HEADLINE>
<P>
SEGAL TO PERFORM IN RANCHO PENASQUITOS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ellen Segal, an ex-Martha Graham principal, will make a guest appearance with 
the Black Mountain Dance Foundation when it performs its annual concert at Mt. 
Carmel High School Theatre in Rancho Penasquitos on June 23-24. 
</P>
<P>
Segal will dance "Without Words," a solo created for her by Erling Sunde. Also 
featured on the concert is Black Mountain Dance Foundation alumnus Michael 
King, a member of Indianapolis Ballet Theatre. 
</P>
<P>
The three-performance run is scheduled for 8 p.m. June 23 and 2 and 8 p.m. June 
24. 
</P>
</TEXT>
