<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: STAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN , Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Singer-actor Howard Keel, saying it has taken him more than 37 years to get 
across town from the MGM lot to the Greek Theatre, will finally make his Los 
Angeles concert performance debut when he appears as a special attraction July 
15 at the Greek. During his years at MGM, he starred in a score of musical 
films, including "Show Boat," "Annie Get Your Gun" and "Seven Brides for Seven 
Brothers." For the last several years, he's been on the lot working as Clayton 
Farlow in the long-running CBS series "Dallas." This fall, he'll be heading out 
for his fifth concert tour in five years of the United Kingdom. ALEENE MacMINN 
</P>
</TEXT>
