<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Picketers from a dozen or so community groups who appeared on KVEA Channel 52's 
doorstep Wednesday in Glendale, and then went inside to protest the alleged 
under-representation of Mexicans and Mexican-Americans in the station's senior 
management, appear to have had at least one of their demands met. Donald G. 
Raider, vice president and chief operating officer of KVEA's parent Telemundo 
network, contacted the demonstrators by telephone from New York and offered to 
meet with their representatives June 28 in Los Angeles, protest organizers 
said. Roxanna Brightwell, a network spokeswoman, confirmed the report. ALEENE 
MacMINN 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
