<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: 8 UCLA EMPLOYEES SEIZED IN DRUG BUSTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Eight UCLA employees were arrested Thursday for allegedly selling marijuana and 
cocaine to an undercover campus police officer, officials at the Westwood 
campus said. Five of the suspects work at the UCLA Medical Center, but none was 
involved in direct patient care, a university spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
The hospital employees arrested were identified by authorities as Ronald Jones, 
47; Rayford Reader, 41; Adrienne Campbell, 37; Fran Hatcher, 32, and Greg 
Pompey, 36. The others arrested were Carolyn Brown, 45; David Franc, 41, and 
Debbie Franc, 37, university police said. Investigators said they had not 
determined whether the Francs were related. 
</P>
<P>
All of the suspects except Brown were arrested on campus, and they all live in 
Los Angeles, the spokesman said. They were booked at the Los Angeles County 
Sheriff's West Hollywood substation for felony possession of drugs for sale, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The largest quantity of drugs allegedly purchased during the six-month 
investigation was two ounces of cocaine, university police said. None of the 
drugs allegedly sold were taken from the hospital, officials said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
