<P>
Broker Barred: The Securities and Exchange Commission has barred a Cincinnati 
stockbroker from the securities business but said he could be reinstated if he 
gets a clean bill of health from a psychiatrist. The broker, P. David 
Herrlinger, caused an uproar on Wall Street in 1987 when he called Dow Jones 
