<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: REAL ESTATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Michael Flagg, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Centennial Group Inc., an Orange developer and home builder, said it recently 
sold about $6.6 million worth of real estate. Analysts and observers said the 
public company may be selling property faster than it would like to dress up 
its bottom line. 
</P>
<P>
The company said its Centennial Estates Inc. unit sold 329 residential lots in 
Lancaster for $5.9 million to Griffin Homes, for a profit of about $1.1 
million. 
</P>
<P>
The company also sold 1.6 acres on Business Center Drive in San Bernardino to 
Robert and Barbara Henley for $689,000 and said it expects a profit of about 
$475,000 on the land, which the company bought in 1979. 
</P>
