<TEXT>
<P>
An engineer inspecting a Pakistan International Airlines plane after an 
emergency landing was crushed to death when the nose gear collapsed, officials 
said today. 
</P>
<P>
The twin-engine Fokker 27 had landed safely on a flight from Bahawalpur on 
Thursday with about 30 passengers and crew after the pilot alerted Sukkur 
airport that instruments showed his nose gear would not lock. Ground engineer 
Akbar Kasim Ali was sent to inspect the nose wheel bay and was working on it 
when the gear collapsed, bringing the plane down on him, airport authorities 
said. He died today of his injuries, they said. 
