<TEXT>
<P>
A coal strike that started in Virginia and triggered wildcat strikes across 
West Virginia reached Pennsylvania today. 
</P>
<P>
Spokesman Hank Waneck of the Rochester &amp; Pittsburgh Coal Co. at Indiana 
said about 1,600 miners left their jobs at midnight, apparently in sympathy 
with the Virginia strikers. Most of the deep coal mines in Indiana County were 
affected by the walkout, Waneck said. Among companies affected were Keystone 
Coal, Helvetia Coal and the Florence Mining Co., all subsidiaries of Rochester 
&amp; Pittsburgh Coal. 
