<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
FORMER COACH HAS HEART TRANSPLANT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MADISON, Wis. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Former University of Wisconsin football Coach John Jardine was listed in 
critical but stable condition today after undergoing a five-hour heart 
transplant operation. 
</P>
<P>
Jardine, 53, who coached the Badgers from 1970 until 1977, was taken into 
surgery Thursday night. He suffered from cardiomyopathy, an illness that 
weakens the heart muscle and enlarges it to two to three times its normal size, 
the hospital said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
